    <h2 id="why-b12">Why B12 Gummies Are Essential for Energy and Brain Health</h2>

    <p>Vitamin B12 (cobalamin) is a water-soluble vitamin that plays an irreplaceable role in DNA synthesis, red blood cell formation, myelin sheath maintenance, and cellular energy production through the citric acid cycle. Unlike most vitamins, B12 is found almost exclusively in animal-derived foods — meat, fish, eggs, and dairy — making supplementation critically important for anyone with limited intake or impaired absorption.</p>

